cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques to detect Mild Cognitive Impairment (MCI) from speech transcripts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of word embeddings also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. The paper also deals with network measurements, which could fall under cs.SD (Systems and Control) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
